<emphasis id="B91D9B259D1F9E02FA31BE1151AAF89B" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="685">C. dilatata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct by the shape of pronotum and metallic green colour of the dorsal side. Sඍൺංඇൾඌ +| Gൺඋർටൺ-Rඈൻඅൾ- ൽඈ (2014) considered both taxa valid and separated 
<taxonomicName id="4C693CB49D1F9E02FA31BE715195F87B" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1875" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cephaloleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="685" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caeruleata">
<emphasis id="B91D9B259D1F9E02FA31BE715195F87B" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="685">C. caeruleata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by antennomere I shorter than III (vs. longer in 
<taxonomicName id="4C693CB49D1F9E02FC8EBEB15197F81B" authorityName="Uhmann" authorityYear="1948" box="[828,940,1983,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cephaloleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="685" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dilatata">
<emphasis id="B91D9B259D1F9E02FC8EBEB15197F81B" box="[828,940,1983,2006]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="685">C. dilatata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), elytral punctures larger laterally (vs. smaller) and prosternum rugose laterally (vs. alutaceous). The figure (fig. 92) they published for 
<taxonomicName id="4C693CB49D1F9E02FB19BEF15705F7DB" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1875" box="[1195,1342,2047,2070]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cephaloleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="685" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caeruleata">
<emphasis id="B91D9B259D1F9E02FB19BEF15705F7DB" box="[1195,1342,2047,2070]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="685">C. caeruleata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not in agreement with the 
<typeStatus id="54D2F9959D199E04FEDBB9B053F3FF18" box="[361,456,190,213]" pageId="20" pageNumber="687">holotype</typeStatus>
and belongs to a completely different species; the figure of 
<taxonomicName id="4C693CB49D199E04FE69B9D05075FF38" authorityName="Uhmann" authorityYear="1948" box="[475,590,222,245]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cephaloleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="687" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dilatata">
<emphasis id="B91D9B259D199E04FE69B9D05075FF38" box="[475,590,222,245]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="687">C. dilatata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was taken from the 
<typeStatus id="54D2F9959D199E04FF0DB9F05325FED8" box="[191,286,254,277]" pageId="20" pageNumber="687">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1617BF9D1E9E03FF25BEDE53AAF7D4" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178059" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5178059" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178059/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="686" startId="19.[151,188,2000,2019]" targetBox="[162,1435,190,1867]" targetPageId="19">
<paragraph id="8BD647379D1E9E03FF25BEDE53AAF7D4" blockId="19.[151,1437,1994,2073]" pageId="19" pageNumber="686">
Figs 8–12. Dorsal aspects. 8–10 – 
<taxonomicName id="4C693CB49D1E9E03FE75BEDE5134F82E" authority="Baly, 1875: 8" authorityName="Baly" authorityPageNumber="8" authorityYear="1875" box="[455,783,2000,2019]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cephaloleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="686" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caeruleata">
<emphasis id="B91D9B259D1E9E03FE75BEDE50A9F82E" box="[455,658,2000,2019]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="686">Cephaloleia caeruleata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF83AC69D1E9E03FD2BBEDE5134F82E" author="BALY J. S." box="[665,783,2000,2019]" pageId="19" pageNumber="686" pagination="73 - 75" refId="ref40869" refString="BALY J. S. 1875: Descriptions of hitherto uncharacterized species of Phytophaga. Entomologist's Monthly Magazine 12: 73 - 75." type="journal article" year="1875">Baly, 1875: 8</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
– holotype, ♀; 9 – ♀ collected by J. Mráz; 10 – J collected by Mráz and compared to the holotype of 
